## 2026-03-27 - CommandPalette token search capped at 100 results with no pagination ‚Äî users with 500+ tokens can't find matches beyond the cap, and there's no indication results were truncated
- Removed the 100-result cap when a search query is active (`tokenQuery` non-empty). All fuzzy-matched results are now returned sorted by score, so users always see every match. The 100-item cap is retained only for the no-query browse mode (when user typed `>` but no search term), where it prevents an overwhelming unfiltered list. Updated the truncation footer message to read "Showing first 100 of N tokens ‚Äî type to search all" and to only appear in browse mode (not during active search).
